latestIgtvVideos.title: Homemade Vitamin-C serum
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
So here it is, the secret tip to make your own Vitamin-C face serum at home, without even spending much in the same.

All you need is 2 oranges and vegetable glycerine. Yes, that's it only 2 ingredients.
Follow the hack and try it today, you will immediately feel the difference.

This will keep fine lines and wrinkles away, as it acts as an anti aging serum as well.

Please to store this serum in refrigerator and use within a week, make fresh for further use.

*Note*-Glycerine is a by-product of soap
manufacture.... Glycerine without a qualifier of the source can be made from any oil or fat, while vegetable glycerine is made only using vegetable oils or fats.
Also use 7-8 drops of mineral water only

latestIgtvVideos.title: Anti-ageing skin tightening home remedy
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
AGING IS A FACT OF LIFE. LOOKING YOUR AGE IS NOT.

I will help with a trick to get you look younger and tighten you skin and get rid of loose skin and wrinkles.

Step 1- Wash your face.
Step 2- Apply egg white on your face.
Step 3- Add lemon drops if you can't bear the smell of an egg.
Step 4- Spread evenly on your face and leave it for 10 mins.
Step 5- Rinse it off with cold water.

You will feel your skin tightened and fresh with the glow.

Comment and review this trick once you use it.

latestIgtvVideos.title: homemade protein shampoo
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
We nowadays are so much use to chemical and sulphate based shampoos as it gives a quick result that we somewhere compromise with our scalp and hair follicles, which later on results in hair fall, dandruff and hair thinning.

So, here I am with my secret shampoo that will be beneficial to keep you away from every problem that your hair may face in future due to excessive use of chemicals.

Ingredients to make protein shampoo:

1 spoon- Amla powder
1 spoon- Shikakai powder
2 spoon- Reetha powder
1 spoon- Rice powder
1 spoon- Flax seed powder

Add 04 glasses of water in saucepan with the ingredients and put it to boil for 20 minutes.
After 20 minutes when 04 glasses of water gets equivalent to 02 glasses of water, strain it into a empty jar.

Ta da, your homemade Protein shampoo is ready. Use it atleast once a week and get the perfect balance between natural and the chemical use of hair products. In long run it will maintain a healthy scalp and hair quality.
